        "title": "Image Quality & Performance",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "High Speed, High Performance",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "45MP CMOS Sensor & DIGIC X",
        "description": "Equipped with an approximately 45-megapixel full-frame CMOS sensor that is compatible with all RF lenses, the EOS R5 will do wonders for your photography with high quality images.\n\nPowered by the latest DIGIC X image processor, the EOS R5 is able to swiftly process large amounts of data to handle high-speed shooting, 8K video and other outstanding achievements possible."
      },
      {
        "title": "Fast & Precise Autofocus (AF)",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "Eye, Face & Head Detection",
        "description": "Similar to the flagship DSLR EOS-1D X Mark III, advanced algorithms in the EOS R5 make it possible to detect and track a subject’s eye, face or head even when the subject is faraway or facing away from the camera."
      },
      {
        "title": "Outstanding Low-light Performance",
        "description": "A hallmark of EOS R system cameras is their outstanding low-light capabilities, and the same applies to the EOS R5, with a native ISO range of 100 to 51200 (expandable to ISO 50 - 102,400), and low luminance AF sensitivity of up to EV -6."
      },
      {
        "title": "Unparalleled Movie Recording Performance",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "8K Video",
        "description": "For the first time ever, you can now record movies in breathtaking 8K RAW/DCI resolution without crop using the entire width of the sensor.\n\nWith 4 times more pixels than 4K videos, not only do you get more detailed and life-like footages, you also enjoy greater creative flexibility in panning, zooming and cropping without loss in resolution when editing your videos."
      },
      {
        "title": "Compatible CFexpress Cards for 8K Recording",
        "description": "Supported"
      },
      {
        "title": "Powerful Image Stabilisation",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "In-Body Image Stabilizer X Optical Image Stabilizer",
        "description": "A new 5-axis In-Body Image Stabilizer in the EOS R5 corrects image blur caused by camera shake, allowing for sharper handheld capture, even with a slower shutter speed.\n\nThis also works in tandem with the Optical Image Stabilizer in the lens, offering stability equivalent to shooting with a shutter speed up to 8 stops* faster, effectively opening up more possibilities for low-light handheld shooting, super-telephoto and long exposure photography."
      },
      {
        "title": "Wireless Connectivity",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "image.canon Cloud",
        "description": "Automatically upload images and video files in their original quality from your EOS R5 to the image.canon cloud-based storage platform for easy access anytime and anywhere, from your PC or smart device.\n\nImage.canon is also compatible with third-party services such as Google Drive, YouTube and Adobe Creative Cloud.\n\n*Information subjected to changes. Refer to https://image.canon/ for latest info."
      },
      {
        "title": "Enhanced Design & Operability",
        "description": ""
      },
      {
        "title": "Dual Card Slots",
        "description": "The EOS R5 doubles your memory capacity with dual card slots that fit one SD card* and one CFexpress card (Type B, up to 2TB size), which is especially necessary when performing 8K recording or high-speed burst shooting."
      },
      {
        "title": "Shot On EOS R5",
